237
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:27,680
<i>Are you a winner or a loser?</i>

238
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:30,690
<i>"I have had many different
jobs during my life.</i>

239
00:20:31,140 --> 00:20:35,900
<i>"My first job was collecting
subway tokens in the subway.</i>

240
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:40,960
<i>"My second job was at Yiddel's
Gourmet Kosher Supplies,</i>

241
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:42,540
<i>"where I worked at the machine</i>

242
00:20:42,540 --> 00:20:45,300
<i>"that made prepackaged
noodle kugels.</i>

243
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:48,740
<i>"I was born Jewish
and used to believe in God</i>

244
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:50,960
<i>"but have since read many books</i>

245
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:55,300
<i>"that have proven God is just
a figment of my imagination.</i>

246
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:56,550
<i>"People like to believe in God</i>

247
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:59,520
<i>"because it answers
complicated questions</i>

248
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:02,600
<i>"like, 'Where did the universe
come from?'</i>

249
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:05,650
<i>"'Do worms go to heaven?'</i>

250
00:21:05,650 --> 00:21:08,610
<i>"'And why do old ladies
have blue hair?'</i>

251
00:21:08,730 --> 00:21:12,560
<i>"Even though I'm an atheist,
I still wear my yarmulke,</i>

252
00:21:12,630 --> 00:21:15,180
<i>"as it keeps my brain warm.</i>

253
00:21:15,210 --> 00:21:18,080
<i>"My third job was for a company</i>

254
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:21,520
<i>"that printed logos
on novelty items.</i>

255
00:21:21,570 --> 00:21:24,870
<i>"I worked at
the Frisbee printing machine.</i>

256
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:28,110
<i>"A Frisbee is
a circular plastic disk</i>

257
00:21:28,110 --> 00:21:30,280
<i>"that people throw
at each other.</i>

258
00:21:30,540 --> 00:21:36,510
<i>"It is like a boomerang,
but it does not come back.</i>

259
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:42,220
<i>"My fourth job was when I was
called up for jury duty.</i>

260
00:21:42,220 --> 00:21:44,010
<i>"I didn't get paid much</i>

261
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:46,230
<i>"but got free cookies
and coffee.</i>

262
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:51,040
<i>"Jurors are outstanding members
of the community</i>

263
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:53,500
<i>"who haven't murdered anybody.</i>

264
00:21:53,690 --> 00:21:56,040
<i>"I made it to the short list
for a trial</i>

265
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:58,640
<i>"where a man killed
all his friends</i>

266
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:01,660
<i>"at his own surprise
birthday party.</i>

267
00:22:02,190 --> 00:22:04,530
<i>"Unfortunately,
I didn't get selected</i>

268
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:09,060
<i>"because they found out I'd been
a mental patient at one point.</i>

269
00:22:09,290 --> 00:22:11,340
<i>"Have you ever been
hang gliding?</i>

270
00:22:12,630 --> 00:22:16,090
<i>"My fifth job was
as a garbage collector.</i>

271
00:22:16,090 --> 00:22:18,180
<i>"I got to clean up
after litterbugs</i>

272
00:22:18,260 --> 00:22:20,430
<i>"and didn't have
to talk to anybody.</i>

273
00:22:20,820 --> 00:22:24,970
<i>"Sometimes I used to pretend
I was an intergalactical robot."</i>

274
00:22:35,750 --> 00:22:36,880
<i>This is 9-1-1.</i>

275
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:39,050
<i>Your call has been placed
in a queue.</i>

276
00:22:39,090 --> 00:22:42,230
<i>"One time, the police
took me in for questioning</i>

277
00:22:42,230 --> 00:22:44,180
<i>"but let me go when they decided</i>

278
00:22:44,190 --> 00:22:47,860
<i>"I wasn't a threat to anybody
except myself.</i>

279
00:22:50,260 --> 00:22:55,520
<i>"The sixth job I had was
for the United States Army</i>

280
00:22:56,050 --> 00:22:58,260
<i>"in the stationery supply
department.</i>

281
00:22:59,470 --> 00:23:01,350
<i>"Because I am good with numbers,</i>

282
00:23:01,470 --> 00:23:05,850
<i>"I had to work out how many
ballpoint pens the Army needed.</i>

283
00:23:05,850 --> 00:23:07,770
<i>"One day they did
a security check</i>

284
00:23:07,940 --> 00:23:11,980
<i>"and asked whether I was
a member of any radical groups.</i>

285
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:14,070
<i>"I told them I was a member</i>

286
00:23:14,070 --> 00:23:16,940
<i>"of the New York
Science Fiction Fan Club.</i>

287
00:23:17,220 --> 00:23:21,100
<i>"They said this didn't count
but dismissed me anyway.</i>

288
00:23:21,570 --> 00:23:24,910
<i>"Fortunately,
I did not remember to tell them</i>

289
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:27,150
<i>"I was once a Communist.</i>

290
00:23:27,150 --> 00:23:30,610
<i>"Have you ever been a Communist?</i>

291
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,490
<i>"Have you ever been attacked
by a crow</i>

292
00:23:32,590 --> 00:23:34,460
<i>"or similar large bird?</i>

293
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:38,420
<i>"When I was nine, a crow
attacked me on my way to school.</i>

294
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:45,200
<i>"I had to have three stitches,</i>

295
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:48,690
<i>"and in spring,
I now wear a helmet</i>

296
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:51,550
<i>"with eyes I have painted on.</i>

297
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:54,190
<i>"People laugh at me
when I wear my helmet,</i>

298
00:23:54,190 --> 00:23:55,730
<i>"but I'm not sure why.</i>

299
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:59,430
<i>"People often confuse me,</i>

300
00:23:59,430 --> 00:24:03,670
<i>"but I try not to let them
worry me.</i>

301
00:24:03,670 --> 00:24:06,910
<i>"New York is a very busy
and noisy place.</i>

302
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:09,970
<i>"I would prefer to live
somewhere much quieter,</i>

303
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:12,310
<i>"like the moon.</i>

304
00:24:12,310 --> 00:24:13,820
<i>"I don't like crowds,</i>

305
00:24:14,030 --> 00:24:17,860
<i>"bright lights, sudden noises,
or strong smells.</i>

306
00:24:18,460 --> 00:24:22,460
<i>"New York has all these,
especially the smells.</i>

307
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:26,860
<i>"I often wear nose- and earplugs
when I go outside.</i>

308
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:31,240
<i>"It helps keep me calm.</i>

309
00:24:31,370 --> 00:24:33,500
<i>"I find humans interesting,</i>

310
00:24:33,620 --> 00:24:36,960
<i>"but I have trouble
understanding them.</i>

311
00:24:37,030 --> 00:24:43,700
<i>"I think, however,
I will understand and trust you.</i>

312
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:45,700
<i>"You appear very happy,</i>

313
00:24:46,050 --> 00:24:49,260
<i>"and I think you would smell
like a shrimp,</i>

314
00:24:49,390 --> 00:24:53,520
<i>"as I know Australia
has a lot of shrimps.</i>

315
00:24:54,010 --> 00:24:55,820
<i>"Can you speed-read?</i>

316
00:24:55,820 --> 00:24:59,200
<i>"I have taught myself to read
two pages at once:</i>

317
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:01,770
<i>"one eyeball per page.</i>

318
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:04,030
<i>"I have to go now,</i>

319
00:25:04,030 --> 00:25:05,310
<i>"even though I have not told you</i>

320
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:09,530
<i>"about my seventh job
in a condom factory.</i>

321
00:25:09,660 --> 00:25:11,280
<i>"Write back soon.</i>

322
00:25:11,410 --> 00:25:13,370
<i>"Your American friend,</i>

323
00:25:13,490 --> 00:25:18,210
<i>"Max Jerry Horowitz.</i>

324
00:25:18,330 --> 00:25:20,000
<i>"P.S., please find enclosed</i>

325
00:25:20,130 --> 00:25:22,380
<i>"a photo
from one of those booths.</i>

326
00:25:23,180 --> 00:25:27,130
<i>"P.P.S., thank you
for the Cherry Ripe,</i>

327
00:25:27,130 --> 00:25:30,640
<i>"and I am glad you like
chocolate as much as I do.</i>

328
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:33,680
<i>"I have never eaten
sweetened condensed milk,</i>

329
00:25:33,810 --> 00:25:36,730
<i>"but I will try some this week.</i>

330
00:25:36,850 --> 00:25:41,360
<i>"P.P.P.S., I have never
used a condom."</i>

331
00:25:46,610 --> 00:25:49,530
<i>Max hoped Mary
would write again.</i>

332
00:25:49,540 --> 00:25:52,370
<i>He'd always wanted a friend,</i>

333
00:25:52,830 --> 00:25:58,240
<i>a friend that wasn't invisible,
a pet, or rubber figurine.</i>

334
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:00,810
<i>He counted the stars</i>

335
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:05,050
<i>and wondered how many days,
hours, minutes</i>

336
00:26:05,170 --> 00:26:08,300
<i>it would take his letter
to reach Australia.</i>

337
00:26:14,150 --> 00:26:17,300
<i>Vera was not impressed...</i>

338
00:26:20,850 --> 00:26:23,980
<i>Not impressed at all.</i>

339
00:26:24,030 --> 00:26:26,320
<i>There was no way this nutcase
was going to be</i>

340
00:26:26,350 --> 00:26:29,730
<i>her daughter's pen-friend,
she thought to herself</i>

341
00:26:29,830 --> 00:26:32,830
<i>There was enough ugliness
in the world.</i>

342
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:34,880
<i>Mary would be home from school
in an hour,</i>

343
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:38,830
<i>enough time for another cup
of tea and a bit of cricket</i>

344
00:26:38,830 --> 00:26:44,700
<i>to soothe the nerves and dissolve the memory
of Max's letter from her pickled mind.</i>

345
00:26:44,740 --> 00:26:45,860
<i>And he's out</i>

346
00:26:45,860 --> 00:26:48,490
<i>found the lead for 14,
England, 7...</i>

347
00:27:20,910 --> 00:27:22,620
Stop!

348
00:27:22,750 --> 00:27:24,580
Wait!

349
00:27:24,710 --> 00:27:28,130
Hey, fellas, you got room
for one more bag?

350
00:27:29,040 --> 00:27:30,380
Sure, Mrs. Dinkle.

351
00:27:30,380 --> 00:27:32,260
Hop in!

352
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:34,140
Good one, Kevin.

353
00:27:39,100 --> 00:27:42,390
Oh.

354
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:45,680
Come on, Vera, we've got
some other bags to pick up.

355
00:27:52,950 --> 00:27:55,280
Hmm.

356
00:27:55,410 --> 00:27:57,830
Hmm.

357
00:27:57,950 --> 00:27:59,240
Mmph!

358
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:02,890
Mary, is that all your rubbish?

359
00:28:03,310 --> 00:28:04,950
Yep!

360
00:28:05,420 --> 00:28:07,210
See ya, toots!

361
00:28:07,910 --> 00:28:10,870
Sweet baby Jesus.

362
00:28:24,380 --> 00:28:26,170
<i>Even though Max's letter</i>

363
00:28:26,190 --> 00:28:28,690
<i>smelled like fish heads
and orange peel,</i>

364
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:33,470
<i>Mary drank his words
like a bowl of alphabet soup</i>

365
00:28:33,530 --> 00:28:37,160
<i>and hadn't been this excited
since Grand-Poppy Ralph</i>

366
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:40,870
<i>had found a coin up her nose.</i>

367
00:28:41,430 --> 00:28:44,740
<i>She wrote back immediately
on some butcher's paper</i>

368
00:28:44,740 --> 00:28:46,670
<i>she'd stolen from some chops.</i>

369
00:28:47,620 --> 00:28:51,840
<i>"Dear Max, I am so excited
you've wroted back.</i>

370
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:54,220
<i>"I don't think
my parents like you,</i>

371
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:55,580
<i>"so from now on,</i>

372
00:28:55,690 --> 00:28:58,890
<i>"send stuff to my neighbour,
Len Hislop,</i>

373
00:28:58,890 --> 00:29:04,020
<i>"at 26 Lamington Drive,
Mount Waverley.</i>

374
00:29:04,140 --> 00:29:06,980
<i>"He's old with no legs.</i>

375
00:29:07,100 --> 00:29:09,990
<i>"They got cheweded off
in World War II</i>

376
00:29:10,070 --> 00:29:14,130
<i>"when some Japanese peoples kept
him in a cage above piranhas."</i>

377
00:29:16,180 --> 00:29:21,200
<i>"Piranhas are goldfish
that have teeth.</i>

378
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:22,870
<i>"He's scared of outside,</i>

379
00:29:22,990 --> 00:29:26,250
<i>"which is a disease
called homophobia."</i>

380
00:29:28,860 --> 00:29:33,490
<i>"He's started giving me 50 cents
a week to get his mail.</i>

381
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:36,470
<i>"I'm saving to buy a castle
in Scotland</i>

382
00:29:36,470 --> 00:29:40,240
<i>"and marry a man
called Earl Grey.</i>

383
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:43,180
<i>"Do you get the Noblets
in America?</i>

384
00:29:43,180 --> 00:29:46,640
<i>"Well, my favourite Noblet
is Vanity Noblet.</i>

385
00:29:47,260 --> 00:29:49,930
<i>"He wants to be
everyone's friend,</i>

386
00:29:49,970 --> 00:29:52,680
<i>"even the boys!</i>

387
00:29:53,020 --> 00:29:56,330
<i>"In your letter,
you said you had no friends.</i>

388
00:29:56,330 --> 00:29:59,880
<i>"Well, neither do I."</i>

389
00:30:01,980 --> 00:30:03,470
<i>"Yesterday at school,</i>

390
00:30:03,470 --> 00:30:06,420
<i>"Bernie Clifford weed
on my Spam sandwich</i>

391
00:30:06,420 --> 00:30:09,210
<i>"and called me poo-face
'cause of my birthmark.</i>

392
00:30:10,140 --> 00:30:14,120
<i>"I wish I could peel it off
like a Band-Aid.</i>

393
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:16,580
<i>"He also laughed,
'cause I had no buttons.</i>

394
00:30:17,230 --> 00:30:19,220
<i>"Ethel pecked them off,</i>

395
00:30:19,220 --> 00:30:20,540
<i>"and Mum couldn't thread
a needle,</i>

396
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:22,800
<i>"'cause she'd been testing
the sherry.</i>

397
00:30:23,260 --> 00:30:27,980
<i>"So she used pegs instead.</i>

398
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:29,720
<i>"When I got home,</i>

399
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:34,600
<i>"I climbed into my secret place
till dinnertime.</i>

400
00:30:34,730 --> 00:30:37,780
<i>"The other kids also laugh
at my haircut.</i>

401
00:30:37,780 --> 00:30:39,830
<i>"Dad has to cut my hair,</i>

402
00:30:39,910 --> 00:30:42,620
<i>"because Mum says
real hairdressers sell your hair</i>

403
00:30:42,620 --> 00:30:46,290
<i>"to Chinamen
who stuff mattresses.</i>

404
00:30:47,700 --> 00:30:52,380
<i>"My teacher, Mrs. Pendergast,
says I should smile more.</i>

405
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:54,020
<i>"I told my mum,</i>

406
00:30:54,100 --> 00:30:58,350
<i>"and so she drawed
a big smile on me.</i>

407
00:30:59,630 --> 00:31:02,220
<i>"I don't think Mrs. Pendergast
likes me anymore.</i>

408
00:31:08,180 --> 00:31:10,020
<i>"I better go now.</i>

409
00:31:10,090 --> 00:31:12,300
<i>"My tears are smudg-ling
my words.</i>

410
00:31:12,990 --> 00:31:14,870
<i>"Your friend in Australia,</i>

411
00:31:14,870 --> 00:31:18,630
<i>"Mary Daisy Dinkle.</i>

412
00:31:18,770 --> 00:31:22,320
<i>"P.S., have you
ever been teased?</i>

413
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:26,030
<i>"Can you help me?</i>

414
00:31:26,030 --> 00:31:30,570
<i>"P.S.S., I've never been
hang gliding before</i>

415
00:31:30,570 --> 00:31:32,330
<i>"or been a Commune-ist</i>

416
00:31:32,370 --> 00:31:34,340
<i>"but would love a Frisbee</i>

417
00:31:34,340 --> 00:31:37,390
<i>"and your recipe
for chocolate hot dogs.</i>

418
00:31:37,670 --> 00:31:43,220
<i>"P.S.S.S., I'm sending you
some Australian chocolate,</i>

419
00:31:43,340 --> 00:31:47,260
<i>"a pompom I made,
and a cake called a Lamington,</i>

420
00:31:47,390 --> 00:31:52,890
<i>"which I was meant to eat
for lunch."</i>

421
00:32:14,540 --> 00:32:18,000
"Have you ever been teased?"

422
00:32:21,420 --> 00:32:23,840
Mary's letter triggered memories

423
00:32:23,840 --> 00:32:25,930
Max had buried deep down
in his shoes.

424
00:32:26,050 --> 00:32:26,970
He's going that way.

425
00:32:27,090 --> 00:32:28,600
We've got him cornered now!

426
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:30,700
Hey, Jew boy, you're gonna pay.

427
00:32:30,700 --> 00:32:32,120
Have a load of this, Jew boy!

428
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:34,570
<i>Jew boy, Jew boy,</i>

429
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:36,780
<i>Jew boy, Jew boy!</i>

430
00:32:39,770 --> 00:32:41,150
<i>And as usual,</i>

431
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:45,490
<i>he coped in the only way
he knew.</i>

432
00:32:54,290 --> 00:32:58,360
<i>And 36
chocolate hot dogs later...</i>

433
00:32:58,460 --> 00:33:01,800
<i>And after only two hours' sleep,</i>

434
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:05,420
<i>Max's meltdown faded away,</i>

435
00:33:05,550 --> 00:33:09,470
<i>and an idea popped
into his brain.</i>

436
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:14,490
<i>"Dear Mary Daisy Dinkle,</i>

437
00:33:14,490 --> 00:33:17,030
<i>"thank you for your letter,
chocolate bar,</i>

438
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:20,170
<i>"Lamington, and pompom.</i>

439
00:33:20,240 --> 00:33:21,950
<i>"The chocolate got crushed,</i>

440
00:33:21,990 --> 00:33:24,700
<i>"so I blended the bits
