00:49:47,020 --> 00:49:50,690
<i>Ivy willed everything
to the local cat shelter,</i>

659
00:49:50,730 --> 00:49:55,560
<i>whose owner relocated her kind
donation to his bank account,</i>

660
00:49:55,690 --> 00:49:59,850
<i>his wife's new breasts,
a Ferrari,</i>

661
00:49:59,850 --> 00:50:02,370
<i>and enough fuel
to get to Mexico.</i>

662
00:50:10,650 --> 00:50:13,990
<i>Despite achieving
all his life's goals,</i>

663
00:50:14,190 --> 00:50:17,650
<i>Max still felt incomplete.</i>

664
00:50:18,940 --> 00:50:23,020
<i>Mr Ravioli just wasn't
cutting the mustard anymore</i>

665
00:50:23,050 --> 00:50:27,770
<i>and seemed more interested
in his self-help books.</i>

666
00:50:27,800 --> 00:50:31,360
<i>Mary had given Max a taste
of real friendship,</i>

667
00:50:31,360 --> 00:50:34,630
<i>and there was just
no comparison.</i>

668
00:50:35,310 --> 00:50:39,810
<i>She missed him too
but no longer saved to see him.</i>

669
00:50:41,630 --> 00:50:45,220
<i>She now saved
for a different reason.</i>

670
00:50:55,560 --> 00:51:01,600
<i>One day, Mr. Ravioli got up,
left, and never came back.</i>

671
00:51:05,320 --> 00:51:09,370
<i>Max sought Dr. Hazelhofs advice.</i>

672
00:51:10,760 --> 00:51:12,940
<i>He told Max that true friendship</i>

673
00:51:13,010 --> 00:51:17,150
<i>is seen through the heart,
not through the eyes,</i>

674
00:51:17,210 --> 00:51:19,590
<i>and that it was time
he wrote to Mary</i>

675
00:51:19,710 --> 00:51:22,350
<i>to reveal his true self</i>

676
00:51:22,350 --> 00:51:24,980
<i>warts and all.</i>

677
00:51:25,400 --> 00:51:26,900
<i>Max understood.</i>

678
00:51:45,610 --> 00:51:48,200
<i>"Dear Mary Daisy Dinkle,</i>

679
00:51:48,320 --> 00:51:51,120
<i>"there is something
I have to tell you</i>

680
00:51:51,240 --> 00:51:55,000
<i>"which will explain why
I have not written.</i>

681
00:51:55,120 --> 00:51:58,070
<i>"Each time I received
one of your letters,</i>

682
00:51:58,070 --> 00:52:01,580
<i>"I had a severe anxiety attack.</i>

683
00:52:01,790 --> 00:52:03,790
<i>"This is because recently,</i>

684
00:52:03,880 --> 00:52:06,160
<i>"while I was
in a mental institution,</i>

685
00:52:06,250 --> 00:52:09,210
<i>"they diagnosed
that I have a new thing</i>

686
00:52:09,260 --> 00:52:13,330
<i>"called Asperger's syndrome,</i>

687
00:52:13,330 --> 00:52:15,660
<i>"which is a neurobiological,</i>

688
00:52:15,730 --> 00:52:20,540
<i>"pervasive,
developmental disability.</i>

689
00:52:20,540 --> 00:52:24,090
<i>"I prefer 'Aspie' for short.</i>

690
00:52:24,320 --> 00:52:28,400
<i>"I will now list
some of the traits of an Aspie.</i>

691
00:52:30,800 --> 00:52:32,370
<i>"Number one:</i>

692
00:52:32,370 --> 00:52:36,120
<i>"I find the world
very confusing and chaotic</i>

693
00:52:36,250 --> 00:52:40,960
<i>"because my mind
is very literal and logical.</i>

694
00:52:44,320 --> 00:52:47,080
<i>"Two: I have trouble understanding</i>

695
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:50,460
<i>"the expressions
on people's faces.</i>

696
00:52:50,900 --> 00:52:52,850
<i>"When I was younger,</i>

697
00:52:52,860 --> 00:52:57,400
<i>"I made a book to help me
when I was confused.</i>

698
00:53:01,820 --> 00:53:05,650
<i>"I still have trouble
with some people.</i>

699
00:53:05,650 --> 00:53:08,990
<i>"Ivy was hard to understand
because of her wrinkles</i>

700
00:53:09,110 --> 00:53:13,370
<i>"and because her eyebrows
weren't real.</i>

701
00:53:13,610 --> 00:53:18,030
<i>"Three: I have bad handwriting,
am hypersensitive...</i>

702
00:53:19,340 --> 00:53:20,800
<i>"Clumsy,</i>

703
00:53:22,020 --> 00:53:24,980
<i>"and can get very concerned.</i>

704
00:53:29,050 --> 00:53:32,680
<i>"Four: I like solving problems.</i>

705
00:53:32,680 --> 00:53:36,230
<i>"Ivy said this is a good thing.</i>

706
00:53:39,410 --> 00:53:41,730
<i>"And finally, number five:</i>

707
00:53:41,730 --> 00:53:45,360
<i>"I have trouble expressing
my emotions.</i>

708
00:53:45,360 --> 00:53:49,630
<i>"Dr. Bernard Hazelhof says
my brain is defective,</i>

709
00:53:49,740 --> 00:53:55,610
<i>"but one day, there will be
a cure for my disability.</i>

710
00:53:55,610 --> 00:53:57,940
<i>"I do not like it
when he says this.</i>

711
00:53:58,070 --> 00:54:01,100
<i>"I do not feel disabled,
defective,</i>

712
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:03,240
<i>"or a need to be cured.</i>

713
00:54:03,240 --> 00:54:06,290
<i>"I like being an Aspie.</i>

714
00:54:06,380 --> 00:54:11,510
<i>"It would be like trying
to change the colour of my eyes.</i>

715
00:54:12,530 --> 00:54:18,030
<i>"There is one thing I wish
I could change, however.</i>

716
00:54:18,270 --> 00:54:20,940
<i>"I wish I could cry properly.</i>

717
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:28,530
<i>"I squeeze and squeeze,
but nothing comes out.</i>

718
00:54:28,640 --> 00:54:32,300
<i>"I cry when I cut onions,
but this does not count.</i>

719
00:54:32,300 --> 00:54:35,130
<i>"Anyway, do you like
the word 'kumquat'?</i>

720
00:54:35,240 --> 00:54:36,990
<i>"It is a type of fruit.</i>

721
00:54:37,420 --> 00:54:40,170
<i>"Do you have
a favourite-sounding word?</i>

722
00:54:40,170 --> 00:54:42,040
<i>"My top five are:</i>

723
00:54:42,160 --> 00:54:44,370
<i>"ointment, bumblebee,</i>

724
00:54:44,500 --> 00:54:49,480
<i>"Vladivostock, banana,
and testicle.</i>

725
00:54:51,150 --> 00:54:55,110
<i>"I have also invented
some new words:</i>

726
00:54:55,290 --> 00:54:57,330
<i>"confuzzled, which is being</i>

727
00:54:57,350 --> 00:55:01,600
<i>"confused and puzzled
at the same time;</i>

728
00:55:02,960 --> 00:55:07,420
<i>"snirt, which is a cross
between snow and dirt,</i>

729
00:55:07,420 --> 00:55:09,360
<i>"and smushables...</i>

730
00:55:10,940 --> 00:55:12,820
<i>"which are squashed groceries</i>

731
00:55:12,820 --> 00:55:15,810
<i>"you find at the bottom
of the bag.</i>

732
00:55:15,810 --> 00:55:19,090
<i>"I have sent a letter
to the Oxford Dictionary people</i>

733
00:55:19,130 --> 00:55:23,320
<i>"asking them to include my words</i>

734
00:55:23,350 --> 00:55:25,680
<i>"but have not heard back.</i>

735
00:55:26,670 --> 00:55:28,600
<i>"It is now time for me to go</i>

736
00:55:28,600 --> 00:55:31,480
<i>"to my Overeaters Anonymous
meeting.</i>

737
00:55:31,540 --> 00:55:34,560
<i>"There is a woman there
called Marjorie Buttersworth</i>

738
00:55:34,630 --> 00:55:36,460
<i>"who confuzzles me.</i>

739
00:55:37,300 --> 00:55:41,340
<i>"She kisses me
without my permission,</i>

740
00:55:41,470 --> 00:55:44,640
<i>"so tonight I have decided
to rub onions</i>

741
00:55:44,710 --> 00:55:47,460
<i>"under my armpits to repel her.</i>

742
00:55:48,130 --> 00:55:55,680
<i>"Your friend in America,
Max Jerry Horowitz.</i>

743
00:55:57,780 --> 00:56:00,570
<i>"P.S., please find enclosed</i>

744
00:56:00,700 --> 00:56:05,410
<i>"some chocolate-covered ants
I found at the deli.</i>

745
00:56:05,430 --> 00:56:09,090
<i>"P.P.S., not much has happened
since I last wrote,</i>

746
00:56:09,240 --> 00:56:12,050
<i>"except for
my manslaughter charges,</i>

747
00:56:12,050 --> 00:56:15,810
<i>"lotto win, and Ivy's death."</i>

748
00:56:19,090 --> 00:56:22,640
<i>Mary was thrilled
Max had finally written</i>

749
00:56:22,760 --> 00:56:25,100
<i>and suddenly had
a fabulous idea.</i>

750
00:56:25,220 --> 00:56:26,390
Aha!

751
00:57:01,390 --> 00:57:05,290
<i>Mary and Max's
friendship was resuscitated,</i>

752
00:57:05,300 --> 00:57:10,210
<i>and her tears were the best gift
he'd ever received.</i>

753
00:57:10,620 --> 00:57:16,040
<i>Inside Max's head,
his brain was smiling.</i>

754
00:57:16,460 --> 00:57:19,090
<i>Loaded up with bizarre forms
of chocolate,</i>

755
00:57:19,160 --> 00:57:21,650
<i>their letters flew
thick and fast</i>

756
00:57:21,660 --> 00:57:23,670
<i>between the continents.</i>

757
00:57:23,670 --> 00:57:26,550
<i>Max learned to read
Mary's letters with caution,</i>

758
00:57:26,670 --> 00:57:30,370
<i>and at the slightest tingle
of tension,</i>

759
00:57:30,370 --> 00:57:33,000
<i>he would stop,
take his medication,</i>

760
00:57:33,080 --> 00:57:35,250
<i>and soothe his nerves.</i>

761
00:57:35,250 --> 00:57:38,970
<i>Each letter he would iron,
laminate,</i>

762
00:57:38,970 --> 00:57:41,140
<i>and file in a special place,</i>

763
00:57:41,180 --> 00:57:45,900
<i>which also soothed his nerves.</i>

764
00:57:49,180 --> 00:57:51,140
<i>He enjoyed answering
her questions</i>

765
00:57:51,140 --> 00:57:53,730
<i>and solving her puzzles like,</i>

766
00:57:53,790 --> 00:57:56,510
<i>"Do sheep shrink when it rains?"</i>

767
00:57:56,690 --> 00:58:00,560
<i>"Why do old men
wear their pants so high?"</i>

768
00:58:00,660 --> 00:58:02,670
<i>"Do gooses get goose bumps?"</i>

769
00:58:02,750 --> 00:58:05,790
<i>"And why is
belly button lint blue?"</i>

770
00:58:06,030 --> 00:58:07,860
<i>"Are there Noblets in heaven?"</i>

771
00:58:07,930 --> 00:58:11,640
<i>"And if a taxi goes backwards,
does the driver owe you money?"</i>

772
00:58:12,540 --> 00:58:15,320
<i>In turn,
Mary simply enjoyed hearing</i>

773
00:58:15,360 --> 00:58:18,490
<i>about Max's fascinating life:</i>

774
00:58:18,630 --> 00:58:21,430
<i>How many people
he'd counted littering...</i>

775
00:58:26,680 --> 00:58:28,810
<i>How the latest Henry had died...</i>

776
00:58:38,420 --> 00:58:42,050
<i>And new recipes
he'd invented for chicken.</i>

777
00:58:45,450 --> 00:58:47,330
<i>Each nourished the other,</i>

778
00:58:47,330 --> 00:58:50,070
<i>and as Mary grew taller,</i>

779
00:58:50,070 --> 00:58:52,270
<i>Max grew wider,</i>

780
00:58:52,350 --> 00:58:59,040
<i>their friendship becoming stronger
than the glue on Mary's Noblets.</i>

781
00:59:02,390 --> 00:59:05,250
<i>Although Max found solace
in Mary,</i>

782
00:59:05,250 --> 00:59:08,750
<i>he still found the rest
of the world bewildering,</i>

783
00:59:08,760 --> 00:59:10,860
<i>and he couldn't understand</i>

784
00:59:10,900 --> 00:59:13,440
<i>why he was seen as the odd one</i>

785
00:59:13,490 --> 00:59:17,240
<i>while everyone else
was considered normal.</i>

786
00:59:18,510 --> 00:59:21,640
<i>Humans were endlessly illogical.</i>

787
00:59:21,810 --> 00:59:23,650
<i>Why did they throw out food</i>

788
00:59:23,700 --> 00:59:27,120
<i>when there were children
starving in India?</i>

789
00:59:27,420 --> 00:59:29,590
<i>Why did they clear
the rain forests</i>

790
00:59:29,590 --> 00:59:32,400
<i>when they needed the oxygen?</i>

791
00:59:32,580 --> 00:59:36,060
<i>And why did they create
bus timetables</i>

792
00:59:36,070 --> 00:59:39,190
<i>when they never ran on time?</i>

793
00:59:39,190 --> 00:59:41,700
<i>He agreed with
his favourite physicist</i>

794
00:59:42,070 --> 00:59:45,200
<i>that there are only
two things infinite:</i>

795
00:59:45,320 --> 00:59:49,200
<i>the universe
and man's stupidity.</i>

796
00:59:51,710 --> 00:59:57,500
<i>And for Mary, even though Max
filled her with confidence...</i>

797
00:59:57,560 --> 00:59:58,410
Bull's-eye!

798
00:59:58,410 --> 01:00:00,800
<i>...her world was far from perfect.</i>

799
01:00:01,970 --> 01:00:05,340
<i>The grip of love
had her by the throat.</i>

800
01:00:26,100 --> 01:00:28,330
<i>At 4:59 p.m.</i>

801
01:00:28,330 --> 01:00:32,340
<i>on the 8th of the 8th, 1988...</i>

802
01:00:33,750 --> 01:00:38,420
<i>Noel Norman Dinkle
attached his last string,</i>

803
01:00:38,540 --> 01:00:42,920
<i>and after 40 years
and 40 million tea bags,</i>

804
01:00:43,050 --> 01:00:44,880
<i>he retired.</i>

805
01:00:45,010 --> 01:00:49,720
<i>To celebrate, Noel announced
he was retiring from taxidermy</i>

806
01:00:49,850 --> 01:00:52,890
<i>and taking up
metal detecting instead.</i>

807
01:00:54,200 --> 01:00:57,650
<i>But sadly, it was not a hobby
he had for long.</i>

808
01:01:34,830 --> 01:01:38,520
<i>In his will,
Noel had left Mary some money,</i>

809
01:01:38,520 --> 01:01:40,650
<i>so she decided
to go to university</i>

810
01:01:40,650 --> 01:01:43,660
<i>and study disorders of the mind,</i>

811
01:01:43,690 --> 01:01:47,400
<i>yearning to learn more
about her friend.</i>

812
01:01:47,450 --> 01:01:50,470
<i>Mary was as popular
at university</i>

813
01:01:50,480 --> 01:01:52,420
<i>as she was at school.</i>

814
01:01:53,740 --> 01:01:57,040
<i>Damian went there too,
aching to be a thespian.</i>

815
01:01:57,280 --> 01:01:59,570
Hi, there, M-M-Mary.

816
01:02:00,080 --> 01:02:02,040
Hi.

817
01:02:02,040 --> 01:02:03,960
Hello.

818
01:02:46,920 --> 01:02:48,970
Hey, Damian,

819
01:02:49,350 --> 01:02:52,790
your mum's roses look fab!

820
01:02:52,790 --> 01:02:55,200
Ah, th-thanks, Mary.

821
01:02:55,270 --> 01:02:57,390
Urn, Mary, can I tell you
something?

822
01:02:57,900 --> 01:02:59,850
Sure, babe!

823
01:02:59,850 --> 01:03:02,270
Um... Um...

824
01:03:02,290 --> 01:03:05,110
you've got d-d-d-dog's poo
on your shoe.

825
01:03:17,450 --> 01:03:21,330
<i>"Dear Max, I have been
such an idiot.</i>

826
01:03:21,460 --> 01:03:23,710
<i>"I've wasted all my money
on something pointless</i>

827
01:03:23,710 --> 01:03:26,760
<i>"when I should have been
saving to see you.</i>

828
01:03:27,680 --> 01:03:29,150
<i>"I know love upsets you,</i>

829
01:03:29,150 --> 01:03:30,910
<i>"so I won't go on about it.</i>

830
01:03:31,010 --> 01:03:34,430
<i>"All I want to say is that
love is obviously not for me.</i>

831
01:03:35,250 --> 01:03:36,620
<i>"I hope you are well</i>

832
01:03:36,620 --> 01:03:39,250
<i>"and enjoy the chocolate
cigarettes I've enclosed.</i>

833
01:03:39,640 --> 01:03:40,560
<i>"Love, Mary."</i>

834
01:03:55,080 --> 01:03:58,530
Oh, you should be ashamed!

835
01:03:58,970 --> 01:04:00,970
Come on, Bethany, let's go.

836
01:04:00,980 --> 01:04:05,210
- Oh, Mom!
- I told you never to talk to strangers, you naughty girl.

837
01:04:13,250 --> 01:04:14,740
<i>Noel's sudden death</i>

838
01:04:14,740 --> 01:04:18,590
<i>had filled Vera
with remorse and guilt,</i>

839
01:04:18,600 --> 01:04:23,430
<i>and she coped
in the only way she knew.</i>

840
01:05:59,110 --> 01:06:00,630
<i>"Dear Max,</i>

841
01:06:00,630 --> 01:06:04,090
<i>"our wedding day was everything
that I've ever dreamt,</i>

842
01:06:04,110 --> 01:06:07,170
<i>"making up
for the terrible year I've had.</i>

843
01:06:09,450 --> 01:06:12,790
<i>"Although all the guests were
Damian's family and friends,</i>

844
01:06:12,790 --> 01:06:14,720
<i>"I felt very welcome.</i>

845
01:06:18,040 --> 01:06:20,000
<i>"Damian is so perfect.</i>

846
01:06:20,050 --> 01:06:22,810
<i>"He even made my wedding dress.</i>

847
01:06:22,940 --> 01:06:24,320
<i>"And for our honeymoon,</i>

848
01:06:24,370 --> 01:06:27,870
<i>"he took me to Mykonos,
his favourite island in Greece.</i>

849
01:06:28,110 --> 01:06:29,570
<i>"I got to ride a donkey</i>

850
01:06:29,610 --> 01:06:32,910
<i>"and found the perfect gift
for Len.</i>

851
01:06:33,140 --> 01:06:34,850
<i>"Poor Len.</i>

852
01:06:34,850 --> 01:06:37,140
<i>"He's still struggling
with his agoraphobia.</i>

853
01:06:45,360 --> 01:06:48,180
<i>"Damian and I are so similar.</i>

854
01:06:48,180 --> 01:06:49,690
<i>"He even has his own pen-friend</i>

855
01:06:49,750 --> 01:06:53,380
<i>"who lives on a sheep farm
in New Zealand."</i>

856
01:06:55,910 --> 01:06:56,860
Mary?

857
01:06:57,670 --> 01:06:59,950
M-M-M-Mary?

858
01:06:59,950 --> 01:07:00,990
Mary?

859
01:07:03,890 --> 01:07:08,430
<i>Mary was bursting
with self-esteem,</i>

860
01:07:08,560 --> 01:07:11,270
<i>and her confidence
was almost unbearable.</i>

861
01:07:13,440 --> 01:07:16,100
<i>At university, she shone</i>

862
01:07:16,100 --> 01:07:17,730
<i>and took it upon herself</i>

863
01:07:17,760 --> 01:07:21,550
<i>to cure the world
of mental illness.</i>

864
01:07:27,970 --> 01:07:31,440
<i>She did her thesis
on Asperger's syndrome</i>

865
01:07:31,490 --> 01:07:35,410
<i>and used Max as her case study.</i>

866
01:07:35,480 --> 01:07:38,290
<i>Her professors
were thoroughly impressed</i>

867
01:07:38,290 --> 01:07:42,090
<i>and her writing
praised far and wide.</i>

868
01:07:42,150 --> 01:07:46,370
<i>Soon, publishers queued
to print her unique insight,</i>

869
01:07:46,370 --> 01:07:48,750
<i>and by her 25th birthday,</i>

870
01:07:48,870 --> 01:07:52,210
<i>thousands of copies
were ready to be shipped.</i>

871
01:07:53,520 --> 01:07:55,320
<i>"Dear Max,</i>

872
01:07:55,320 --> 01:08:01,000
<i>"I am very proud to give you the very first
copy of my book about your disability</i>

873
01:08:01,000 --> 01:08:03,630
<i>"and the hopes that we have
to one day cure it.</i>

874
01:08:05,850 --> 01:08:08,480
<i>"Even more exciting is that
I'm finally coming</i>

875
01:08:08,530 --> 01:08:12,570
<i>"to meet and celebrate with you
in one week's time.</i>

876
01:08:12,690 --> 01:08:15,780
<i>"I'm also gonna give you
half the royalties.</i>

877
01:08:15,780 --> 01:08:19,400
<i>"Your loving friend, Mary.</i>

878
01:08:19,450 --> 01:08:25,120
<i>"P.S., please find enclosed some
chocolate-coated Swiss almonds."</i>

879
01:08:28,640 --> 01:08:31,480
<i>Max didn't take
the news very well...</i>

